{
  "stem": "13469.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And within the family, she has always and will always be called Eve.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "But, for some reason, in the Jewish survivor community in London, she's known as Rachel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "I think she went to a place-- Lingfield House-- once, where there was another Eve.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And in order to not mix up the two Eves, Eve one and Eve two, our Eve decided to be called Rachel.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And she's now known by most people in the London survivor community as Rachel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "So, excuse me if I carry on calling her Eve because it's very difficult for me to call her Rachel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I shall mix it all up kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Eve was born.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And having been born in London, she was British.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, we always thought that she was British, just like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But again, I've thought about that more recently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What we had, later on in the camps-- and if it wasn't for this business that Eve was born in London, I wouldn't be sitting here today.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But she was a British citizen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had her birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I have a copy of it here amongst our documents.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She never had a British passport.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At the time, until quite recently, I hadn't realized that there was a difference between having a British passport and having a British birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But, at that time, we just assumed she was British.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and that helped us enormously later on at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now another question that we never asked our parents is whether this is why we went to London.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because, obviously, Eve was born in June.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we went to London in February.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Obviously, my mother was pregnant by that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And therefore, they knew that there was going to be a birth.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
